      There are countless horror stories of bad relations between contractors and clients that ruin construction projects. With fresh scars from a previous project we embarked on looking for a contractor to extensively remodel our home with trepidation and anxiety.

      We needn't have worried because Ciaran came into our life like a brilliant ray of sunshine piercing the gray San Francisco fog.

      We are delighted with the extensive home remodel project Ciaran did for us. His costs are fair, and he is very easy to communicate with and responded almost immediately by phone and text whenever we needed him.

      Ciaran is very easy to get along with, and consistently demonstrated his mission to ensure we were happy with his work. He's also quite the comedian who can defuse potentially frustrating situations with his friendly humor and banter.

      There were a few inevitable surprises in the project which Ciaran handled with aplomb and resolved to our satisfaction, even when the issue was not "his problem", e.g. he diagnosed and fixed the leak in a new bathtub.

      We highly recommend talking with Ciaran if you're considering a construction project.

      When friends, family and neighbors ask about our remodel, they anxiously wait for the remodel horror story..and give me that look of ok....let me hear about the drama. Because, I'm sure you've heard very scary and dramatic remodel stories... my response has and will always be..I love my contractor. Ciaran Dowler, owner of Edenavow. He's like the guy you grew up with that everyone liked and wanted to be around. Thank goodness he's handy, funny, ethical, man of his word and charming.

      We live in an old a$$ Spanish Mediterranean SF home, built in 1927. We interviewed 3 contractors and Ciaran was the last one... he came into our home was like freaking santa clause so damn excited about the remodel and had such great ideas (even though we had an architect/design team)! If I gave him just a hint of a thought, he turned it into a reality. "what do you think of this space, Ciaran.. "you know what? I'd knock this wall down create and arch and it would be gorgeous" ...and hot damn was it! Ciaran and his team built the most beautiful arches in my home, I'm waiting for arch digest to call me!

      Now onto the details...We gutted our kitchen (well the crew did not me..but I really wanted to and I think Ciaran would have let me), knocked down walls, moved bathrooms, made a master bath, updated electrical (that dang knob and tube) rerouted plumbing and HVAC and insulated and sheet rocked our garage.

      Want to hear the best part? We lived in the home while this was happening.. ok that's not really the ideal but we aren't swimming in cash. I was so nervous of the dust and the whatever's as we lived downstairs with 3 kids. Ciaran and his guys always left the home swept up w/ that shop vac and had this magic plastic door placed so whatever debris and dust from upstairs didn't end up down.

      The crew was something else, Sandor, Juan, Joel, Phillip all professional, fun and great craftsmen. The sub-contractors, the same! Goes without saying that the subs are also very very important part of your remodel so thankfully Ciaran has some great friends in the industry.

      Here are some photos so you don't think I'm one of Ciaran's family members...also I didn't get paid for this review I've just been waiting so long to write it! Thank you Ciaran and team... my family and I love our home!

      Having had a bad experience with our previous renovation, I would have laughed my head off if anyone ever mentioned "a stress-free renovation". But this was before I had Ciaran and his team from Edenavow Construction work on our kitchen and bathroom remodeling. We are so happy with them.
      Ciaran and his team are professional, friendly, respectful and reliable. They really made sure that all the work was top quality and completed within a reasonable time. I truly don't think that I've had a single unpleasant incident with them. That is not to say that there were no mishaps - there were a couple of minor things - but Ciaran and his team addressed them immediately. The crew always kept the site very clean and were very accommodating when we could not have any noise in the house (this was during pandemic with zoom meetings) When these guys said they were coming over, they would arrive on the dot (I still can't get over this!). We were so impressed with them that we ended up expanding our original remodeling plan to refinish our living room, dining room and one of the bedrooms.
      Ciaran is very good with wood work and he made a beautiful custom made closet for our odd shaped bathroom for a reasonable price. Their services may not be the cheapest, but I really feel that expense was well worth the quality of work we received.
      Reading over this, I realize that this review looks suspiciously like something I wrote in exchange for a discount, but Ciaran didn't even ask me for a review. I just honestly feel that I owe Ciaran and his team a great review for doing such a great job.

      We are delighted with the beautiful cabinet that Ciaran built for us that fit snugly in the odd-shaped corner of our bathroom.
